3. Overload Selection Algorithm
Created: New file 

interpreter/runtime/overload.go
 (195 lines)

Core function: 

SelectBestOverload(methodName string, candidates []*MethodDefinition, args []RuntimeValue)

Algorithm:

Filter candidates by parameter count
Score each viable candidate based on type compatibility
Select candidate with highest score
Return error if ambiguous (multiple candidates with same score)
Scoring logic (

scoreParameterMatch
):

Exact match: 1000 points (e.g., string → 

String
)
Null match: 100 points (null can match any reference type)
Generic exact: 900 points (e.g., List<Account> → List<Account>)
Generic compatible: 500 points (e.g., List<Account> → List<SObject>)
Subtype match: 200 points (inheritance/interface)
Incompatible: -1 (filtered out)
Key features:

Array canonicalization: String[] → List<String> for uniform comparison
Generic type extraction: Parses List<Account> to extract element type Account
Case-insensitive: Apex is case-insensitive, so string matches 

String
Subtype checking: Validates class hierarchy (e.g., all custom types are 

SObject
 subtypes)
4. Lookup Site Updates
Updated: 15+ method and constructor lookup sites to use 

SelectBestOverload

Pattern:

// Before: Direct lookup
if method, ok := classDef.Methods[methodName]; ok {
    return ctx.InvokeMethod(className, method, args)
}
// After: Overload selection
if candidates, ok := classDef.Methods[methodName]; ok {
    method, err := ctx.SelectBestOverload(methodName, candidates, args)
    if err != nil {
        return Null(), err
    }
    return ctx.InvokeMethod(className, method, args)
}
